nd race specific trends in health and disability. Demography and the Economy explores the connections between demography and economics, paying special attention to what demographic trends can reveal about the sustainability of traditional social security programs and the larger implications for economic growth. The volume brings together some of the leading scholars working at the border between the two disciplines, and it provides an eclectic overview of both fields. Contributors also offer deeper analysis of a variety of issues such as the impact of greater wealth on choices about marriage and childbearing and the effects of aging populations on housing prices, Social Security, and Medicare.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aDemographyxEconomic aspects. 0aFertility, HumanxEconomic aspects. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh1 aAttanasio, Orazio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBillari, Francesco C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBörsch-Supan, Axel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoda, Gopi Shah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHartnett, Caroline Sten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIsen, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Larry E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKitao, Sagiri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLudwig, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoterba, James M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPreston, Samuel H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchieber, Sylvester J., econtributor.4ctb